{"id":"1708.03219","submitter":"Mohamadreza Ahmadi","authors":"Mohamadreza Ahmadi, Giorgio Valmorbida, and Antonis Papachristodoulou","title":"Safety Verification for Distributed Parameter Systems Using Barrier\n  Functionals","comments":"Preprint under review at Systems and Control Letters. arXiv admin\n  note: text overlap with arXiv:1603.08716","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.OC","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  We study the safety verification problem for a class of distributed parameter\nsystems described by partial differential equations (PDEs), i.e., the problem\nof checking whether the solutions of the PDE satisfy a set of constraints at a\nparticular point in time. The proposed method is based on an extension of\nbarrier certificates to infinite-dimensional systems. In this respect, we\nintroduce barrier functionals, which are functionals of the dependent and\nindependent variables. Given a set of initial conditions and an unsafe set, we\ndemonstrate that if such a functional exists satisfying two (integral)\ninequalities, then the solutions of the system do not enter the unsafe set.\nTherefore, the proposed method does not require finite-dimensional\napproximations of the distributed parameter system. Furthermore, for PDEs with\npolynomial data, we solve the associated integral inequalities using\nsemi-definite programming (SDP) based on a method that relies on a quadratic\nrepresentation of the integrands of integral inequalities. The proposed method\nis illustrated through examples.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 9 Aug 2017 05:25:07 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-08-11"}
